  "time_ut": 1660453964,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dd4 3\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0db1 \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0dbb\u0dab 1110\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "1110 elephant deaths under 3 years",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Due to the conflict between wild elephants and human beings, many lives of wild elephants as well as human lives have been destroyed in various parts of the island. Elephant-human conflicts have increased in the last three years. Accordingly, 407 elephant deaths and 122 human deaths in 2019, 328 elephant deaths and 112 human deaths in 2020, 375 elephant deaths and 142 human deaths in 2021 have also been reported.",
        "In the first 4 months of 2022, 47 elephant deaths and 34 human deaths have been reported due to elephant-human conflict. Of these wild elephant deaths, 13 were shot, 17 were due to electrocution, 19 were due to hook attacks and 8 were due to injuries.",
        "A discussion regarding the prevention of elephant-human conflicts in Hambantota district was held yesterday (13) under the chairmanship of the Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera at the Lunugamwehera Wildlife Office. Wildlife officers and others participated in this event.",
        "It was revealed here that the elephant-human conflict exists in 131 regional secretariat jurisdictions in 19 districts located in 08 provinces of Sri Lanka.",
        "The Minister observed that the necessary equipment for the construction of electric elephant fences to cover all areas where wild elephants are threatened in the Hambantota district has been available in the Lunugamwehera Wildlife Office for some time. Nevertheless, it was revealed that the construction of the electric fence remains a problem due to some farmers' organizations as well as farmers protesting against the construction of the electric elephant fence, and that the equipment brought for the purpose has not yet been put to proper use.",
        "In this way, it has been confirmed that the equipment brought to set up electric fences in the wildlife offices all over the island has not been properly utilized.",
        "Therefore, as a step to end the human-elephant conflict in the forest within the next year, the Minister advised the Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation Secretary Mrs. Chandra Herath that an agreement should be reached in consultation with all farmer organizations and farmers, and to prepare an urgent work order for that.",
        "Also, although wild elephants are included in the list of animals that damage crops, steps should be taken to include them in the category of protected animals, and in the future, in the preparation of development projects, land located in areas with a lot of wild elephants will not be given to them, the minister said."
      ],
